# User Testing & Feedback
We shared our sprint 1 Figma prototype to 2 portential users for testing and to get feedback.

# Key Feedback
User 1:
1. During the writing of the report, the user noted that having to type the whole address was tedious and wanted there to be an "Auto-detect location" feature.
2. The user liked the ability to take a photo directly in the app but asked for a Gallery option so that they can report an issue that they photogrpahed earlier in the day.
3. The user mentioned that they would feel more motivated to use the app if they could see a fixed status on their reports so they know that the council is actually taking action. 

User 2:
1. The user stated that seeing a lot of pin pointed reports on the map was overwhelming so they suggested that to add a priority filter based on how serious the report actually is. 
2. The user found the map view with all the reported pins helpful, but the user suggested that when a pin is clicked it should show the attached photo immediately without opening a new page.
3. The user stated that they would like to edit their report just in case they made a mistake and have already submitted the report.
